# Cross-platform line-ending policy (a collaborator on Windows, the owner on Linux).
# Repo blobs are normalized to LF; Windows checkouts may show CRLF locally,
# but what lands in git is always LF so nothing breaks on the other side.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Scripts that MUST stay LF or they fail on Linux ("bad interpreter").
# The repo is already LF throughout, so this just locks current behavior in
# (no renormalization churn). .bat/.ps1 run fine with LF on Windows too.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf

# Gradle's gradlew.bat was committed with literal CRLF. Freeze it byte-exact
# (-text = no EOL conversion ever) so it never churns or shows as modified.
eve-app/android/gradlew.bat -text

